A mutilated body of a man was found on the Matokomane and Matlatsi mountains outside Burgersfort. Cops have launched a massive manhunt for the suspects involved in the brutal murder. Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said the gruesome discovery was allegedly made by a passerby who then alerted the police. The police found the mutilated body with some body parts missing. Ngoepe said the man was wearing only a blue jean, the suspects are still unknown at this stage and there is no arrest. The motive behind this incident is still unknown but ritual-related killing may not be ruled out. Ngoepe urged anyone with information that can lead to the arrest of the suspects involved in this matter to contact Colonel Mahlathini Lazarus Ngele on 082 5733 645 or the Crime Stop number 08600 10111.